{"title": "In Old Plantation Days", "description": "With this collection of short stories, Dunbar sought to draw on the success of his dialect poems by recreating and portraying the southern plantation during slavery. The stories focus on the stereotypical portrait of slaves as obedient workers happy to spend their lives in service of their benevolent owner. His attempt to find success was only partially realized, as his stories drew not only criticism but, in some cases, anger at their very stereotypical nature. The book itself, however, proved to be more lucrative than previous fiction works had been for the author. (Summary by Special Collections and Archives, Wright State University)", "duration": 20775, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "546", "name": "Paul Laurence Dunbar"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/in_old_plantation_days_2105_librivox/oldplantationdays_2105.jpg", "copyright_year": "1903", "genres": ["Culture & Heritage Fiction", "Historical Fiction", "Short Stories"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "Jim Locke"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Jim Locke"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "DaveC"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "DaveC"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "Aunt Tempe's Triumph", "readers": [10801], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/in_old_plantation_days_2105_librivox/inoldplantationdays_01_dunbar_64kb.mp3", "duration": 777}, {"section": 2, "title": "Aunt Tempe's Revenge", "readers": [10801], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/in_old_plantation_days_2105_librivox/inoldplantationdays_02_dunbar_64kb.mp3", "duration": 892}, {"section": 3, "title": "The Walls of Jericho", "readers": [10801], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/in_old_plantation_days_2105_librivox/inoldplantationdays_03_dunbar_64kb.mp3", "duration": 891}, {"section": 4, "title": "How Brother Parker Fell from Grace", "readers": [10801], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/in_old_plantation_days_2105_